covered: Valid Request: Scenarios TC01 and TC02 exercise updating with valid payloads and verify 204 response.
Partial Update: TC19 demonstrates updating only provided fields.
Non-Existing Resource: TC08 covers handling when account does not exist (400).
Concurrency Issues: TC17 tests concurrent updates to the same account.
Authorization: TC09 covers unauthorized access; headers presence validated in multiple scenarios (TC01/TC02/TC04).
Server Error Handling: TC12 simulates database unavailability leading to 500.
Validation/Invalid Data: TC07 and TC21 cover invalid account data and input formats.
Large Payloads: TC13 tests large payloads; TC02 covers full-field updates.
Extra Query Parameters: TC22 checks handling of unexpected query parameters.
Empty Request Body: TC11 tests missing body leading to 400.
Missing Required Header: TC05 validates missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header leading to 400.
Extra, Unsupported Fields: TC10 ensures only supported fields are updated.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests address rate limiting or throttling behavior under burst requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache-related behavior.
Pagination: PUT typically does not paginate, but guidelines mention pagination; no relevant test scenario exists for output pagination in PUT context.
Edge-case: Systematic testing of treatNullAsReset combinations across multiple fields (beyond TC03/TC04) could be expanded.
Integration/Propagation: While TC16 touches dependent services, broader end-to-end propagation across multiple downstream services and failure modes could be expanded.
Performance under load: TC17 addresses concurrency but lacks explicit performance/throughput assertions under load (timing/latency metrics).
recommendations: Add rate limiting/throttling tests for PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId} to ensure proper throttling and graceful degradation under high request volume.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on PUT responses and verify cache invalidation/consistency behavior when accounts are updated.
Document and test a broader set of edge-case null-handling across multiple fields to strengthen treatNullAsReset coverage.
Expand end-to-end integration tests to include more dependent services and failure modes, ensuring correct fallback/compensation behavior.
Incorporate explicit performance/latency assertions under simulated load to satisfy the Performance criteria in guidelines.
